"At the end of April, one of the world's biggest dark websites, Dream Market, was shut down. Whatever the reasons, it's unlikely to make a serious long-term dent in what is estimated to be a trillion-dollar industry. The dark web and the cybercrime economy it facilitates are a phenomenon of our times, offering all the tools and resources that cyber criminals need to launch attacks on consumers and organisations, and a ready-made platform on which to sell their wares."
